1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,010 --> 00:01:37,720
=Episode 8=

3
00:02:09,610 --> 00:02:10,620
(My Queen)

4
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:26,510
(My Queen)

5
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,319
We found a house we like.

6
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:37,800
But we are short over a million.

7
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,759
I just hoped Ming could help.

8
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:42,000
After all, Ming is Weijie's cousin.

9
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:43,120
Cousin?

10
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,120
Has Qian Weijie ever

11
00:02:44,199 --> 00:02:45,120
treated Yu Ming like one?

12
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:46,080
Whatever you say,

13
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:47,520
they are still cousins.

14
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,719
Related by blood.

15
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:50,120
Do not play that card with me.

16
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,080
You think I do not know

17
00:02:51,159 --> 00:02:51,960
what you are after?

18
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,879
I know exactly

19
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:53,520
what you're thinking.

20
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:54,439
You saw those two

21
00:02:54,479 --> 00:02:55,039
come into money,

22
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,400
so now you want their deposits

23
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:57,240
to hit your targets.

24
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:58,479
That is selfish,

25
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,360
and hypocritical.

26
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,080
I am selfish?

27
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:02,400
Funny.

28
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:03,240
Let me tell you.

29
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,039
I'm helping them

30
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,319
manage their money.

31
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:06,039
And I'm selfish?

32
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:07,319
You're also trying to drag them

33
00:03:07,439 --> 00:03:08,759
into your tutoring business?

34
00:03:09,479 --> 00:03:10,080
You fraud.

35
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,719
Fraud?

36
00:03:10,759 --> 00:03:12,439
I am helping Yitong start a business.

37
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:13,360
What do you know?

38
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,000
How dare you

39
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,159
call that helping?

40
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:16,800
Help her?

41
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,599
Where were you before?

42
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,439
How can you even say that?

43
00:03:19,479 --> 00:03:20,520
Where were you before?

44
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,039
Listen.

45
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:22,840
We are family.

46
00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:24,319
Blood is thicker than water.

47
00:03:24,439 --> 00:03:25,439
What are you?

48
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,319
What am I?

49
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,599
We are colleagues

50
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:28,560
who help each other,

51
00:03:28,719 --> 00:03:30,080
and work as one team.

52
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:30,479
Got it?

53
00:03:30,479 --> 00:03:31,919
Please. Colleagues?

54
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:32,560
Weren't you

55
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,759
the one who gave Yitong

56
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,680
a hard time?

57
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:35,560
Keep your hands off me.

58
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:36,639
I know everything.

59
00:03:36,719 --> 00:03:37,800
Before this, did you ever

60
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,960
treat Yu Ming as your family?

61
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,800
None of your business.

62
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,719
That is our family matter.

63
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,560
And you'll go broke

64
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:41,960
running that

65
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:42,840
tutoring business.

66
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:46,039
Watch your mouth.

67
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,919
No one touches that money

68
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,240
without my approval.

69
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:50,719
Oh, come on.

70
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:52,240
I already told you.

71
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,199
It is about family.

72
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,439
Not money.

73
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:56,520
Family!

74
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,879
Family, my foot.

75
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,120
A million?

76
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,080
Do you think Yitong

77
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,240
runs a bank?

78
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,840
How can you

79
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:04,199
talk like that?

80
00:04:04,199 --> 00:04:05,120
So ungrateful.

81
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,080
I have been speaking up

82
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,479
for Yitong all day.

83
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,800
Do not talk about banks.

84
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,479
That money

85
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:11,039
belongs to our Wenwen.

86
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,560
Why should it all be Wenwen's?

87
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:13,919
They're not even divorced yet.

88
00:04:14,319 --> 00:04:14,759
Then divorce!

89
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,879
Now!

90
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,120
Good heavens!

91
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:17,879
Sis,

92
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,399
can you stop talking

93
00:04:19,439 --> 00:04:20,720
about divorce all day?

94
00:04:20,879 --> 00:04:21,759
Better to save a marriage

95
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:23,240
than tear one apart.

96
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:24,279
Besides,

97
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,319
the two of them

98
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:27,199
are trying to have a baby now.

99
00:04:27,319 --> 00:04:28,120
A baby?

100
00:04:28,199 --> 00:04:28,879
I am telling you,

101
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:29,879
in this lifetime,

102
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,480
Wenwen is the only child
they'll ever have.

103
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,560
Deposits? These days?

104
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,800
How old-fashioned.

105
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
With your luck,

106
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,519
you'll go broke.

107
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:49,000
Yu Ming.

108
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:50,639
Get out of my way.

109
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:51,399
You are back.

110
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,439
Stay away from my bro.

111
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,680
Ming, let me manage your money.

112
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:55,959
Yitong has stood by you for years.

113
00:04:55,959 --> 00:04:57,439
Now it is your turn to back her.

114
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:59,279
Money in hand brings peace of mind.

115
00:04:59,319 --> 00:04:59,680
Ming.

116
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,839
The tutoring market is still

117
00:05:00,879 --> 00:05:02,279
a pie waiting to be sliced.

118
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,720
Ming, saving money is discipline.

119
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:05,160
It is your strongest safety net.

120
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:05,480
Ming.

121
00:05:05,519 --> 00:05:06,079
Save what?

122
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,360
Money you spend is wealth.

123
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,040
Money you don't spend
is just inheritance.

124
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:09,839
Move.

125
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,160
Let me do it.

126
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:12,000
- Let me.
- Let me.

127
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:12,480
Me.

128
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:13,160
Enough!

129
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:15,680
Bro.

130
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:16,839
Who is your bro?

131
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:18,199
Me?

132
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:19,560
Or money?

133
00:05:21,079 --> 00:05:21,560
And you.

134
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,680
Have you forgotten

135
00:05:22,839 --> 00:05:23,439
how you treated me?

136
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,519
How you

137
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,199
treated my wife?

138
00:05:25,279 --> 00:05:25,759
How dare you

139
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:26,519
ask me to invest in you?

140
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,240
Don't you

141
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:27,879
have GPS?

142
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,040
Know your place.

143
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:32,759
Oh! Yitong is home!

144
00:05:32,759 --> 00:05:33,360
Yitong.

145
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,160
Only now?

146
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,879
The ultrasound clinic is almost closed.

147
00:05:40,879 --> 00:05:42,160
Enjoy your checkup.

148
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:44,079
Liar.

149
00:05:55,639 --> 00:05:56,319
Are you sober yet?

150
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,040
Yes.

151
00:05:57,079 --> 00:05:57,759
Fully sober?

152
00:05:57,879 --> 00:05:58,319
Completely.

153
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:58,959
Last night,

154
00:05:58,959 --> 00:05:59,720
what did you

155
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,160
promise me?

156
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:00,800
Do you remember?

157
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:01,319
I remember.

158
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,000
Then say it.

159
00:06:04,759 --> 00:06:06,279
There's nothing
between me and Liu Xinlu.

160
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:09,120
I need to drink less and stay grounded.

161
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,240
That's key.

162
00:06:12,079 --> 00:06:12,959
The singing monkey.

163
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,279
I'm telling you.

164
00:06:16,279 --> 00:06:17,439
None of these people mean well.

165
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,399
They are not here for you.

166
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,480
They're here for the money.

167
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,879
You need to separate the wolves

168
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:21,519
from the sheep.

169
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,319
Yes.

170
00:06:23,079 --> 00:06:23,839
I have my principles.

171
00:06:24,439 --> 00:06:25,120
I'll delete

172
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,199
Liu Xinlu.

173
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,839
Can we call this matter

174
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,439
done and over with?

175
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,319
Then I have news for you.

176
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:38,439
There was a fire at Unit 505.

177
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:40,319
Someone deliberately set it
with gasoline.

178
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,480
Back to the shop.

179
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:19,959
Text Yu Ming.

180
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:21,680
Send him all the photos you took.

181
00:07:22,319 --> 00:07:23,480
Commit to the act.

182
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:25,000
Think long term.

183
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,879
If you play your cards right,

184
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,360
the money is yours.

185
00:07:29,079 --> 00:07:29,560
Right?

186
00:07:30,639 --> 00:07:31,160
Send it.

187
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,519
Dear Ming.

188
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:45,480
Are you awake?

189
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,360
Feeling better?

190
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:48,079
Look at you.

191
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:50,000
Why did you drink so much last night?

192
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,040
Is Tong mad at you?

193
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,319
Last night,

194
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:55,079
I think she misunderstood us.

195
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,879
Do you need me to explain for you?

196
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,279
He blocked me.

197
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:18,279
Here comes the cake.

198
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,279
This cranberry one is sweeter

199
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:21,680
than the blueberry.

200
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,720
Everyone, try some.

201
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:23,519
Ouyang.

202
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,680
I have diabetes.

203
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:25,680
Can I eat this?

204
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,199
Do not worry. I prepared yours.

205
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:28,639
This is whole wheat, no sugar.

206
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,120
The walnuts inside are very healthy.

207
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,519
It's easy on the stomach.

208
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:32,080
It's okay.

209
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:32,639
Okay.

210
00:08:33,519 --> 00:08:34,639
You know what?

211
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:35,960
When you eat cake,

212
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,480
you've got to have music with it.

213
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:38,960
You see those Westerners?

214
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,039
That is how they do it.

215
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,320
Nuo is not here today.

216
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,320
If she were here,

217
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:42,840
then we'd

218
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,039
have music, right?

219
00:08:44,679 --> 00:08:45,360
Where is Nuo?

220
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,279
Where did she go?

221
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:49,039
Nuo.

222
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:51,000
You arrived.

223
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,440
What happened? You look terrible.

224
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:54,679
I am fine.

225
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,519
Wait a moment.

226
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,120
Is Nuo low on blood sugar?

227
00:09:08,639 --> 00:09:10,240
You should take her out more.

228
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,159
Let her get some sun.

229
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:11,480
Yes.

230
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,240
Good for calcium.

231
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,879
She is a little too thin.

232
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,120
It is fine, madam. You eat first.

233
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:15,879
I will talk to her.

234
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:16,600
All right.

235
00:09:19,279 --> 00:09:19,960
Thank you.

236
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,240
What exactly happened?

237
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,159
My landlord kicked me out.

238
00:09:31,399 --> 00:09:31,960
Why?

239
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:33,840
He'll rent it out.

240
00:09:39,759 --> 00:09:40,639
What will you do?

241
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,120
Stay here for tonight, I guess.

242
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,039
There's a spare room.

243
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:49,080
Where are you planning to rent next?

244
00:09:50,519 --> 00:09:51,919
I'll see after I get paid next month.

245
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,679
I gave him all the money I had.

246
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,039
I have an extra room at my place.

247
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,039
You can rent from me.

248
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:02,080
Utilities are all included.

249
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,200
It is on the island.

250
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:04,480
As for rent,

251
00:10:05,039 --> 00:10:05,840
no rush.

252
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,720
Pay me whenever you have it.

253
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:09,039
Think about it.

254
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:10,740
♪Sunlight falls through the curtains♪

255
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,780
♪Softly kissing your face♪

256
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,860
♪Like a secret♪

257
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:19,030
♪A little secret♪

258
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,559
♪Whenever we're together♪

259
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,080
Thank you.

260
00:10:22,679 --> 00:10:23,759
What happened to your cello?

261
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:25,240
It was fine yesterday.

262
00:10:26,470 --> 00:10:28,500
♪A little understanding♪

263
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:31,520
♪Our bond growing deeper♪

264
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,559
The landlord tried to keep it.

265
00:10:34,919 --> 00:10:36,519
It broke when I tried to take it back.

266
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:38,930
♪I see the stars shining♪

267
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,620
♪Listening to your heartbeat♪

268
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:44,450
♪Such a special rhythm♪

269
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,440
Thank you.

270
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,230
♪I'm falling for you♪

271
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:51,279
♪Now baby I love you♪

272
00:10:51,279 --> 00:10:51,799
Your helmet.

273
00:10:51,799 --> 00:10:54,870
♪Now baby I love you♪

274
00:10:55,340 --> 00:10:59,700
♪And I just need you too♪

275
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:03,190
♪Every second♪

276
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,850
♪Every minute, every day♪

277
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:07,920
♪I want to be by your side♪

278
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:13,270
♪The moments that steal my heart♪

279
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:16,850
♪Whenever we're together♪

280
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,770
♪Another perfect day♪

281
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:21,600
♪Rain or shine♪

282
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:25,040
♪As long as I'm with you♪

283
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,120
Yu Ming.

284
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,000
That motorcycle behind us...

285
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:45,960
I noticed it long ago.

286
00:11:46,679 --> 00:11:47,720
He is following us.

287
00:11:49,639 --> 00:11:51,039
Is he after our money too?

288
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:51,960
I don't know.

289
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,519
We cannot go back to the shop now.

290
00:11:54,399 --> 00:11:55,519
Should I slam the brakes

291
00:11:55,519 --> 00:11:56,320
and send him flying?

292
00:11:56,639 --> 00:11:57,080
No.

293
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:58,919
Then should we...

294
00:11:58,960 --> 00:11:59,480
No.

295
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:00,759
Then what?

296
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,279
Speed up. Circle around.

297
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,360
Okay.

298
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:48,080
Hello?

299
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:50,480
I am on him.

300
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,200
He is in the restroom.

301
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,759
♪Work hard and make money♪

302
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:56,200
♪I want to get rich♪

303
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,360
♪A villa by the sea♪

304
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,080
♪Seafood every day♪

305
00:14:50,879 --> 00:14:51,960
Come on. Come on.

306
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,039
It is stuck.

307
00:14:58,279 --> 00:14:59,039
Hurry. Hurry.

308
00:15:08,159 --> 00:15:09,240
The streetlight is broken.

309
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,039
It might be dark

310
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:10,919
when you come back.

311
00:15:11,279 --> 00:15:12,440
I'll have someone fix it tomorrow.

312
00:15:12,759 --> 00:15:13,480
If you feel scared

313
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:13,960
coming back,

314
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,879
call me and I'll come

315
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,159
get you.

316
00:15:18,679 --> 00:15:19,279
This is my place.

317
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:26,799
Come in.

318
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:30,440
Here, let me.

319
00:15:31,159 --> 00:15:31,679
Thank you.

320
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,399
My stepmom and I

321
00:15:36,399 --> 00:15:37,159
decorated this place.

322
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:39,120
So you may see

323
00:15:39,679 --> 00:15:40,679
quirky stuff around.

324
00:15:41,799 --> 00:15:43,039
My parents divorced early.

325
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,159
Later, they both

326
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:45,000
remarried.

327
00:15:45,279 --> 00:15:46,639
So now I have

328
00:15:46,679 --> 00:15:48,200
two dads and two moms.

329
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,360
They all get along well.

330
00:15:49,799 --> 00:15:50,679
Usually though,

331
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,039
I barely get to see any of them.

332
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:53,720
This is my bedroom.

333
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:55,399
Let me put your cello inside.

334
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,120
You can stay there.

335
00:15:57,519 --> 00:15:58,080
What about you?

336
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,519
I will sleep upstairs.

337
00:16:02,279 --> 00:16:03,080
Kitchen's over there.

338
00:16:10,279 --> 00:16:11,440
Guess they're afraid I'll starve.

339
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:12,960
So they keep sending food over.

340
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,200
But most of it

341
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,399
is what they like to eat.

342
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,480
Feel free to cook

343
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,120
whatever you want.

344
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:25,590
(Ride safely)
(Drink water. Eat well. Sleep early.)

345
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:26,519
Damei.

346
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:28,399
Damei, there you are.

347
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,080
Come here.

348
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,000
Damei.

349
00:16:33,279 --> 00:16:34,120
You have a cat?

350
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:34,720
Yes.

351
00:16:34,919 --> 00:16:36,000
She is my stepmom's cat.

352
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,720
When she got her,

353
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,440
she was tiny.

354
00:16:37,759 --> 00:16:38,559
Then she got huge.

355
00:16:38,559 --> 00:16:39,600
So her name means "Big Beauty."

356
00:16:40,679 --> 00:16:41,039
Yes.

357
00:16:43,639 --> 00:16:44,519
She's a little naughty.

358
00:16:44,559 --> 00:16:45,559
She is shy around new people.

359
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:51,679
Excuse me.

360
00:16:54,039 --> 00:16:54,840
Fire inspection?

361
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,120
You cannot reach Yu Ming?

362
00:16:57,679 --> 00:16:58,480
All right.

363
00:16:58,519 --> 00:16:59,440
What time tomorrow?

364
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:00,799
Okay.

365
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,119
Get some rest.

366
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,119
I may need to step out.

367
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,119
The showerhead is a bit tricky,

368
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,160
just so you know.

369
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,240
Let the water run for a while,

370
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:09,960
or it will be cold.

371
00:17:10,759 --> 00:17:11,839
And the sheets and covers

372
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,440
are on the top shelf of the closet.

373
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:14,240
I'll take you

374
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:15,160
to the landlord tomorrow,

375
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,240
and get all your stuff back.

376
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:16,880
Don't worry.

377
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:48,119
Where's the girl living here?

378
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,599
Who are you?

379
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,920
I asked where the girl is.

380
00:17:55,359 --> 00:17:56,319
She moved out.

381
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,200
Where did she move?

382
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,359
Does she owe you money too?

383
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:02,880
That shameless girl.

384
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,000
Always causing trouble.

385
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,200
Does she owe everyone money?

386
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:06,880
What are you doing?

387
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:07,720
Who are you?

388
00:18:08,359 --> 00:18:08,880
Let go.

389
00:18:09,079 --> 00:18:09,680
Let go.

390
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,480
I'll call the police.

391
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:11,799
You...

392
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:12,559
Go ahead.

393
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:13,640
Just wait.

394
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:14,759
You dare

395
00:18:14,799 --> 00:18:16,400
hit people in broad daylight?

396
00:18:20,559 --> 00:18:21,079
Stop it!

397
00:18:21,279 --> 00:18:22,240
Stop. Stop.

398
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:22,720
Please stop!

399
00:18:23,119 --> 00:18:24,000
Stop hitting him!

400
00:18:24,359 --> 00:18:25,599
I am begging you!

401
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:26,880
Stop this!

402
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:29,880
We can talk this through.

403
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:30,680
Please stop.

404
00:18:31,039 --> 00:18:31,720
Call them, go on/

405
00:18:31,839 --> 00:18:32,960
I won't. I won't call.

406
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:33,599
I'm not calling.

407
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,440
Please.

408
00:18:34,559 --> 00:18:35,920
Stop hitting him.

409
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:40,600
(Chen Zinuo)

410
00:18:48,430 --> 00:18:51,210
(Du Lei)

411
00:18:59,279 --> 00:19:00,240
Just to be safe,

412
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,240
I've already turned off my phone.

413
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,279
So they can't track us.

414
00:19:05,039 --> 00:19:06,119
Who do you think

415
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:07,079
is following us?

416
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,799
Could it be Hong Jinkui?

417
00:19:10,319 --> 00:19:10,960
No, no.

418
00:19:12,279 --> 00:19:13,559
That person's build

419
00:19:13,799 --> 00:19:15,640
was not as huge as Hong Jinkui's.

420
00:19:16,319 --> 00:19:17,440
He could hire someone.

421
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:19,839
Who knows

422
00:19:19,839 --> 00:19:20,480
about tbe lottery?

423
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:21,200
How many?

424
00:19:23,039 --> 00:19:24,279
Quite a few.

425
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,880
Auntie's family.

426
00:19:27,759 --> 00:19:29,079
Song Youcheng.

427
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:29,920
Song Youcheng.

428
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,799
The lottery shop owner.

429
00:19:31,839 --> 00:19:32,559
Mr. Xiang.

430
00:19:32,559 --> 00:19:33,119
Right.

431
00:19:33,119 --> 00:19:33,680
Here.

432
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:34,759
Write them down.

433
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:36,359
Who else? Anywhere else?

434
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:38,200
Some other lottery players.

435
00:19:39,319 --> 00:19:40,440
A lot, really.

436
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,119
Write them. Every single one.

437
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:50,240
Someone broke into our villa before.

438
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,680
One with long hair,

439
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,000
one with short hair.

440
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,160
One tall,

441
00:19:56,519 --> 00:19:57,240
one short.

442
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:57,920
Four people?

443
00:19:58,759 --> 00:19:59,720
Two.

444
00:19:59,759 --> 00:20:01,359
One man, and one woman.

445
00:20:01,559 --> 00:20:02,920
Why didn't you tell me?

446
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:03,880
Was that before

447
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:04,599
or after the lottery?

448
00:20:04,759 --> 00:20:05,200
Before.

449
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,279
That means

450
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,519
these people probably knew

451
00:20:09,759 --> 00:20:11,200
there was money in the villa, right?

452
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,039
Right.

453
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,079
It was on the news too.

454
00:20:16,319 --> 00:20:18,160
A pair of thieves, a man and a woman.

455
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:18,960
They're on the run.

456
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,839
A man and a woman.

457
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:24,039
Good thing we moved the money.

458
00:20:24,119 --> 00:20:24,799
Now no one knows

459
00:20:24,799 --> 00:20:25,440
where it is.

460
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:26,400
Safe. For now.

461
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:27,759
Write those names down first.

462
00:20:28,359 --> 00:20:29,359
As long as we stay careful

463
00:20:29,359 --> 00:20:30,279
cautious, we'll be fine.

464
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,279
Ouyang.

465
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:24,839
How bold.

466
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,000
Hello, Ms. Zhang.

467
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:33,920
Hi, Ms. Wen.

468
00:21:34,319 --> 00:21:35,079
Can you

469
00:21:35,079 --> 00:21:36,119
come to the school?

470
00:21:36,319 --> 00:21:36,799
What happened?

471
00:21:37,799 --> 00:21:38,680
Wenwen is acting a bit

472
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:40,440
strange.

473
00:21:41,119 --> 00:21:41,799
One more for you.

474
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,079
Another one. Not this one.

475
00:21:47,079 --> 00:21:47,480
Thank you.

476
00:21:49,839 --> 00:21:51,160
Wu Xiaoxuan, give me a pair.

477
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,119
Wu Xiaoxuan, trade with me.

478
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:55,359
Look at these little monsters.

479
00:21:55,359 --> 00:21:55,960
Aren't they cute?

480
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:56,920
Mine has them too.

481
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,240
Your monster's eyes are so pretty.

482
00:21:58,759 --> 00:21:59,640
Mine has them too.

483
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,440
Those eyes...

484
00:22:10,519 --> 00:22:11,079
Okay. Okay.

485
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,400
Sorry for the trouble.

486
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,119
These red socks...

487
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,279
Why so many red socks?

488
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,279
Wenwen?

489
00:22:16,759 --> 00:22:17,359
I bought them.

490
00:22:18,759 --> 00:22:19,599
How many did you buy her?

491
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:22,799
Fifty or sixty?

492
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,319
Twenty to thirty pairs?

493
00:22:25,079 --> 00:22:25,799
Fifty or sixty sets.

494
00:22:26,039 --> 00:22:26,960
Fifty or sixty pairs.

495
00:22:27,119 --> 00:22:27,799
Why did you buy her

496
00:22:27,799 --> 00:22:28,799
so many red socks?

497
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:30,319
She likes them.

498
00:22:32,079 --> 00:22:32,480
What?

499
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,319
She caused trouble.

500
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,480
Did she wear all fifty or sixty pairs

501
00:22:37,519 --> 00:22:39,160
on her feet at once?

502
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,160
Is she a centipede?

503
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,200
No, she handed them out.

504
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:42,119
She drew monsters

505
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:42,839
on every pair

506
00:22:42,839 --> 00:22:43,720
and handed them out.

507
00:22:43,759 --> 00:22:44,720
Don't know where she gets it.

508
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,599
I am going to the school.

509
00:22:45,599 --> 00:22:46,359
Just grab a cab back.

510
00:22:46,359 --> 00:22:46,680
Hurry.

511
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,960
She was sharing with others.

512
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,480
How is that "causing trouble"?

513
00:22:51,759 --> 00:22:52,920
Stop wasting my time. Hurry up.

514
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:53,839
Do not drag this out.

515
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,079
She is being kind.

516
00:23:08,359 --> 00:23:08,960
Hello.

517
00:23:09,079 --> 00:23:11,000
The number you dialed is powered off.

518
00:23:19,599 --> 00:23:20,839
How can you keep the money here?

519
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:28,960
The fire inspector is coming.

520
00:23:29,839 --> 00:23:30,759
I'll hold it for you first.

521
00:23:31,359 --> 00:23:32,440
Put it in the bank soon.

522
00:24:03,359 --> 00:24:04,000
What is this?

523
00:24:04,279 --> 00:24:05,000
Need a hand?

524
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:05,599
No.

525
00:24:20,119 --> 00:24:20,640
Hello?

526
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:34,759
I'm off to the nursing home.

527
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:35,680
Don't wait for me.

528
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:36,839
Okay.

529
00:24:37,559 --> 00:24:38,279
Want me to drive you?

530
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:39,519
No need.

531
00:24:39,799 --> 00:24:40,480
I can go myself.

532
00:25:29,359 --> 00:25:29,839
Xiu.

533
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,079
Did you see anyone go into my shop?

534
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:32,720
Ouyang came by

535
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,039
several times.

536
00:25:34,559 --> 00:25:35,799
Lucky he came by more than once.

537
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,119
Your place is a mess.

538
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,599
Fire inspection is tomorrow.

539
00:25:38,799 --> 00:25:40,079
And he couldn't reach you by phone.

540
00:25:47,599 --> 00:25:49,039
Did you take it?

541
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:51,519
Where is it?

542
00:25:51,799 --> 00:25:52,480
Where are you?

543
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,119
Right next to you.

544
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,200
Why would you do this?

545
00:26:04,359 --> 00:26:04,680
I...

546
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:05,680
Because you are jealous.

547
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,039
You cannot stand seeing me

548
00:26:07,039 --> 00:26:08,039
richer than you.

549
00:26:08,039 --> 00:26:09,799
You want to be rich too, don't you?

550
00:26:09,799 --> 00:26:11,480
Fine. Everyone likes money.

551
00:26:11,559 --> 00:26:12,599
You saw all that cash.

552
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,920
You could have left me some.

553
00:26:14,039 --> 00:26:15,000
Or talked to me first.

554
00:26:15,119 --> 00:26:16,880
So why take every last bit of it?

555
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:17,720
Why?

556
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:18,759
I...

557
00:26:18,759 --> 00:26:19,640
Because you are selfish

558
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,799
at heart.

559
00:26:20,799 --> 00:26:21,920
Because you never

560
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,319
treated me like a brother.

561
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,720
If you needed money,

562
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:25,440
you could've told me.

563
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:26,559
I would have shared it with you.

564
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,799
But taking all of it?

565
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:28,319
That's just

566
00:26:28,359 --> 00:26:29,519
too ugly.

567
00:26:31,799 --> 00:26:32,400
What do you mean?

568
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:34,759
Chen Zinuo.

569
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:35,160
Hang up.

570
00:26:36,359 --> 00:26:37,359
So it was her.

571
00:26:37,599 --> 00:26:38,599
She put you up to it.

572
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:39,720
She told you to take

573
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,599
all my money, didn't she?

574
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,599
You are good by nature.

575
00:26:41,599 --> 00:26:42,799
I didn't expect someone so vile

576
00:26:42,799 --> 00:26:43,960
to be pulling

577
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:44,559
your strings.

578
00:26:44,559 --> 00:26:46,119
You chose a woman over your brother.

579
00:26:46,359 --> 00:26:47,720
No, it is worse than that.

580
00:26:47,759 --> 00:26:49,079
You crushed brotherhood,

581
00:26:49,079 --> 00:26:49,839
trampled on it,

582
00:26:49,839 --> 00:26:51,079
and let it blow away in the wind.

583
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:52,480
You're seriously messed up.

584
00:26:52,519 --> 00:26:53,559
After all these years,

585
00:26:53,559 --> 00:26:54,440
this is how you treat me?

586
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,200
Let me tell you.

587
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,079
The money in that villa

588
00:26:56,079 --> 00:26:56,640
is mine.

589
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:57,960
It has nothing to do

590
00:26:57,960 --> 00:26:58,519
with Chen Zinuo.

591
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,359
This money came from the villa?

592
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:04,279
Yes.

593
00:27:04,799 --> 00:27:05,680
You never won the lottery,

594
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,119
did you?

595
00:27:06,519 --> 00:27:07,160
So what?

596
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,319
You stole Chen Zinuo's family

597
00:27:09,319 --> 00:27:09,880
money.

598
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:11,039
You stole from her family.

599
00:27:11,039 --> 00:27:11,440
Nonsense.

600
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,279
You did steal from them.

601
00:27:12,279 --> 00:27:13,039
Her family's money?

602
00:27:13,039 --> 00:27:13,519
Do you know

603
00:27:13,519 --> 00:27:14,279
how hard she has it?

604
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:15,880
All the money in that house is mine.

605
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:21,519
I'll call the police

606
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,160
right now!

607
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:23,079
My treasure.

608
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:23,759
I'll call them.

609
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:24,720
Go ahead.

610
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,799
You have really lost your mind.

611
00:28:01,319 --> 00:28:02,799
These drawings are so ugly.

612
00:28:02,799 --> 00:28:03,839
All teeth and claws.

613
00:28:03,839 --> 00:28:04,440
Why?

614
00:28:04,799 --> 00:28:05,400
My drawings

615
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,599
are the worst in my class.

616
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:07,680
I draw ugly things

617
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,079
because the people I see are ugly.

618
00:28:09,599 --> 00:28:10,599
What kind of talk is that?

619
00:28:11,119 --> 00:28:12,400
Who exactly do you see that's ugly?

620
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,440
Am I ugly? Or your dad?

621
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,039
Anyone with money in their eyes.

622
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,640
So you are the pretty one.

623
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,920
Can I have a pair of those socks?

624
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,000
You just said they're ugly.

625
00:28:31,759 --> 00:28:32,680
I am not ugly.

626
00:28:32,799 --> 00:28:34,039
So what if they're ugly?

627
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,960
You should read fewer books.

628
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:36,480
You'll be

629
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,720
the neighborhood philosopher.

630
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:39,839
No idea who you take after.

631
00:28:40,039 --> 00:28:41,279
Definitely not you or my dad.

632
00:28:43,359 --> 00:28:44,279
I should kick you out.

633
00:28:45,839 --> 00:28:46,720
Then give me back the socks.

634
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,559
Look at these.

635
00:28:47,559 --> 00:28:48,480
One big, one small.

636
00:28:48,799 --> 00:28:50,799
This is cheap garbage.

637
00:28:51,279 --> 00:28:52,839
These two aren't even a pair.

638
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,960
Give me a matching pair.

639
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,440
This is clean.

640
00:29:10,519 --> 00:29:11,640
Why rush to change?

641
00:29:15,559 --> 00:29:16,119
He's gone.

642
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:17,400
Return home?

643
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,000
Oh.

644
00:29:36,119 --> 00:29:37,200
If you had some money,

645
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,359
a lot of money,

646
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:39,759
how would you spend it?

647
00:29:40,039 --> 00:29:40,680
There is no "if."

648
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,759
Just pretend there is.

649
00:29:44,519 --> 00:29:45,240
What would you do?

650
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:46,920
You want the truth?

651
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:48,160
Yes.

652
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:53,559
I would burn it.

653
00:29:56,119 --> 00:29:57,519
Someone hanged himself in Unit 505.

654
00:29:58,640 --> 00:29:59,279
I know.

655
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:01,240
That was my dad.

656
00:30:03,039 --> 00:30:03,880
The police said

657
00:30:04,599 --> 00:30:05,720
he was strangled with a rope.

658
00:30:06,519 --> 00:30:07,319
I don't think so.

659
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:09,680
What do you think?

660
00:30:15,559 --> 00:30:16,119
It was money.

661
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:26,319
What's meant to be yours

662
00:30:27,839 --> 00:30:29,039
will always be yours.

663
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:42,559
You are back.

664
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:43,000
Min.

665
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:43,640
Back from school.

666
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:44,680
Yitong.

667
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,079
Dad.

668
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:46,880
Go upstairs first.

669
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:47,759
I need to talk to your mom.

670
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,599
Take this up with you.

671
00:30:49,799 --> 00:30:50,880
Let Grandma try on the clothes.

672
00:30:51,279 --> 00:30:51,799
Why are you

673
00:30:51,799 --> 00:30:52,599
sneaking around here?

674
00:30:54,039 --> 00:30:54,519
What happened?

675
00:30:54,599 --> 00:30:56,279
Ouyang took

676
00:30:56,279 --> 00:30:58,440
our money.

677
00:30:58,720 --> 00:30:59,240
Why?

678
00:30:59,279 --> 00:31:00,440
There was a fire inspection.

679
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:01,440
The community office called,

680
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:01,920
but I missed it.

681
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,000
Then they called him.

682
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:03,519
He went over,

683
00:31:03,519 --> 00:31:04,440
saw all that money,

684
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,319
and took it away.

685
00:31:05,359 --> 00:31:06,440
I asked for it back but failed.

686
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,720
Then we got into it.

687
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:08,960
Wait.

688
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:09,559
He won't go crazy

689
00:31:09,559 --> 00:31:10,400
for money.

690
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:12,000
Yeah, but he knows that money

691
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:13,400
didn't come from a lottery win.

692
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,160
It was hidden inside the wall.

693
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,480
So he says that money belongs to

694
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:17,079
Chen Zinuo,

695
00:31:17,119 --> 00:31:18,160
and refused to give it back.

696
00:31:18,519 --> 00:31:19,559
Has love gone to his head?

697
00:31:19,559 --> 00:31:20,839
Come on. Let us get it back.

698
00:31:22,279 --> 00:31:23,000
Anywhere else hurt?

699
00:31:23,119 --> 00:31:23,559
No.

700
00:31:23,559 --> 00:31:24,200
He's no match for me.

701
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,160
He may look worse than I do.

702
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,839
I have a place on the east side.

703
00:31:31,119 --> 00:31:31,640
It is spacious,

704
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:33,240
south-facing.

705
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:36,240
Chaoming Park is right downstairs.

706
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,079
It's very convenient.

707
00:31:39,799 --> 00:31:40,839
I mentioned it before.

708
00:31:42,359 --> 00:31:43,079
Go stay there.

709
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:44,279
It is safe.

710
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:46,839
I am not in danger now.

711
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,279
Living in someone else's home

712
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,319
is never convenient.

713
00:31:52,039 --> 00:31:53,240
And your place isn't my home either.

714
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:57,680
Zinuo.

715
00:31:59,599 --> 00:32:01,200
After what happened to Mr. Chen,

716
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,400
a sum of money went missing.

717
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,319
No one knew

718
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,240
where it had gone.

719
00:32:06,839 --> 00:32:07,799
Not even the police.

720
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,799
That money was meant for you.

721
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:23,960
Can you imagine

722
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,000
my dad hanging there?

723
00:32:31,319 --> 00:32:32,039
When someone

724
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:33,839
hangs themselves,

725
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:36,759
the muscles of the tongue relax.

726
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,119
The jaw opens from the pressure.

727
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,599
The tongue falls out.

728
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:44,559
Drool drips down.

729
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,519
And the body loses control.

730
00:32:49,519 --> 00:32:50,440
I can't understand it.

731
00:32:53,119 --> 00:32:54,720
My father was such a clean man.

732
00:33:00,519 --> 00:33:00,960
Don't ever

733
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:01,839
bring this up to me again.

734
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:03,200
Please.

735
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:06,839
Whatever he left behind,

736
00:33:08,279 --> 00:33:09,160
it has nothing to do with me.

737
00:34:07,799 --> 00:34:08,519
Ranran!

738
00:34:09,559 --> 00:34:10,280
Ranran!

739
00:34:15,119 --> 00:34:15,559
Ranran.

740
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:16,800
Ranran!

741
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,719
Who is she to you?

742
00:34:32,239 --> 00:34:33,039
My little sister.

743
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,320
What is her name?

744
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:39,519
Ranran.

745
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:41,960
Ranran.

746
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:42,639
Brother.

747
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,639
Ranran, I am here.

748
00:34:45,599 --> 00:34:46,400
Open the door, please.

749
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:48,199
I can't wash it off.

750
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:50,000
Ranran.

751
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:51,159
I can't.

752
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:54,519
I can't get clean.

753
00:34:55,430 --> 00:34:57,660
(Kill)

754
00:35:34,719 --> 00:35:35,960
Ranran was timid.

755
00:35:38,239 --> 00:35:39,639
(Sun Leran's Grave)
Just seeing a cockroach

756
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:42,079
(Sun Leran's Grave)
would make her jump into my arms.

757
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:45,239
When she jumped into the sea,

758
00:35:46,519 --> 00:35:47,960
how much courage must that have taken?

759
00:35:52,679 --> 00:35:53,440
It is over now.

760
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:55,880
Change your name.

761
00:35:58,719 --> 00:35:59,679
From now on, you are Du Lei.

762
00:35:59,730 --> 00:36:01,960
(Du Lei)

763
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,719
(Du Lei)
Leave the honesty

764
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:05,639
to me and Zinuo.

765
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:07,920
You must protect her.

766
00:36:08,559 --> 00:36:10,119
Don't let anyone hurt her.

767
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,800
From this day on,

768
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,559
Zinuo is your sister.

769
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,280
You must become her way out.

770
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:19,559
Her last resort.

771
00:36:37,679 --> 00:36:38,079
We're here.

772
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:39,400
I live here.

773
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:41,960
Why insist on living here?

774
00:36:45,079 --> 00:36:45,760
Because of the fridge.

775
00:36:46,559 --> 00:36:47,119
The fridge?

776
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:50,880
He has two dads

777
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:52,119
and two moms.

778
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,400
The fridge holds four people's care.

779
00:36:58,800 --> 00:36:59,679
I never knew

780
00:37:01,079 --> 00:37:01,639
a fridge could

781
00:37:01,639 --> 00:37:02,760
hold so much.

782
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:07,039
The cushions on the sofa

783
00:37:07,599 --> 00:37:08,199
look like the sun.

784
00:37:10,119 --> 00:37:11,039
Holding it feels warm.

785
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:15,400
You can buy those things.

786
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:18,000
No, you can't.

787
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:22,639
I never had that.

788
00:37:24,119 --> 00:37:24,679
Not once.

789
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,519
Damei, dinner time.

790
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:45,159
Damei.

791
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:47,480
I knew you'd be here.

792
00:37:49,119 --> 00:37:50,000
Come on, let's go eat.

793
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:52,199
Here.

794
00:38:16,159 --> 00:38:17,199
If you had some money,

795
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:18,400
a lot of money,

796
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:19,440
what would you do?

797
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,079
I can tell

798
00:38:20,079 --> 00:38:22,480
you left in a hurry.

799
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:23,920
After what happened to Mr. Chen,

800
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:25,679
a sum of money went missing.

801
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:27,280
Go back to sleep.

802
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,199
What's meant to be yours

803
00:38:29,079 --> 00:38:30,039
will always be yours.

804
00:38:30,039 --> 00:38:31,320
That money was meant for you.

805
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:00,599
Ouyang.

806
00:39:03,519 --> 00:39:04,159
Ouyang.

807
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:19,760
Look, I...

808
00:39:20,159 --> 00:39:21,159
I owe you an apology.

809
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:22,199
I went too far today.

810
00:39:22,559 --> 00:39:23,480
But I need to tell you,

811
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:25,320
the money in that house

812
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,079
really belongs to me.

813
00:39:26,159 --> 00:39:27,480
There is a contract.

814
00:39:27,679 --> 00:39:28,239
It says

815
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,639
everything in the house,

816
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:31,480
even construction waste, is mine.

817
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:32,719
It is written in black and white.

818
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,880
Construction waste is not money.

819
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:35,400
Ming,

820
00:39:36,159 --> 00:39:37,000
that money is not clean.

821
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:37,719
You don't know that?

822
00:39:38,039 --> 00:39:39,559
I looked into Chen Liyang's case.

823
00:39:39,719 --> 00:39:40,800
It's still not closed.

824
00:39:41,519 --> 00:39:42,440
The thirty million?

825
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:42,960
No one knows

826
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,559
where it went.

827
00:39:43,639 --> 00:39:44,280
Then those money

828
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:45,119
turns up in your villa.

829
00:39:45,119 --> 00:39:46,000
It is the same amount.

830
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,000
Don't you find that strange?

831
00:39:47,079 --> 00:39:47,840
Holding onto it now,

832
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:48,760
don't you feel dangerous?

833
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,079
Look, whether this money

834
00:39:50,079 --> 00:39:50,719
is clean or not,

835
00:39:50,719 --> 00:39:51,840
you can't just take it

836
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,000
and keep it for yourself, right?

837
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:54,280
Even if, for argument's sake,

838
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:55,639
the money does belong to Chen Zinuo,

839
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:56,599
shouldn't it be her

840
00:39:56,599 --> 00:39:57,280
telling us that?

841
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,320
So why did you two end up

842
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:58,719
like this?

843
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,039
How could she possibly talk to you?

844
00:40:00,239 --> 00:40:00,719
Ouyang.

845
00:40:04,079 --> 00:40:04,920
Good. You are here.

846
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:06,079
Tell him yourself.

847
00:40:06,079 --> 00:40:07,119
The things in Unit 505...

848
00:40:07,159 --> 00:40:08,000
you... you...

849
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:08,599
I don't want it.

850
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:12,679
You don't have to keep

851
00:40:12,679 --> 00:40:13,199
testing me.

852
00:40:15,159 --> 00:40:15,840
Don't worry.

853
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:17,559
I won't take a single cent of it.

854
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,239
You heard Chen Zinuo.

855
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,360
She does not want the money.

856
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,079
We still have to find a way

857
00:40:27,079 --> 00:40:28,199
to get it back from Ouyang.

858
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,639
I will talk to Ouyang again.

859
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:36,400
It really is packed.

860
00:41:49,559 --> 00:41:50,599
Is this the cushion

861
00:41:50,599 --> 00:41:51,679
Zinuo mentioned?

862
00:42:01,639 --> 00:42:02,360
Is it warm?

863
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,880
(Next Episode)

864
00:43:08,199 --> 00:43:09,440
(Actress, Ren Suxi)
I'm Ren Suxi.

865
00:43:09,679 --> 00:43:11,519
(Actress, Ren Suxi)
I invite you to watch Wonder Wall.

866
00:43:13,159 --> 00:43:13,800
Fan Meijuan?

867
00:43:14,239 --> 00:43:14,679
Mom,

868
00:43:14,679 --> 00:43:15,519
Be careful.

869
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:16,760
You're her family?

870
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:17,320
I know.

871
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:18,079
That's her bag.

872
00:43:18,079 --> 00:43:18,840
It's fine.

873
00:43:20,039 --> 00:43:22,719
It's a 100% match.

874
00:43:22,840 --> 00:43:25,960
She came from nowhere
and saved your mom.

875
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:29,039
Did we dig through?

876
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:33,840
This doesn't look like a basement.

877
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:35,119
Zhu.

878
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:35,800
That's money!

879
00:43:55,610 --> 00:44:02,620
♪The road ahead is still so long
Where have you gone?♪

880
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:11,340
♪Under the blazing sun
I keep heading north♪

881
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:20,220
♪To those who pass me by
You don't have to look at me♪

882
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:28,640
♪Just keep walking your own way
I'll manage on my own♪

883
00:44:31,630 --> 00:44:35,230
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

884
00:44:35,870 --> 00:44:39,000
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

885
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:44,940
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

886
00:44:44,940 --> 00:44:47,930
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

887
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:52,250
♪Can I change my mind?♪

